Only 5,000 guests will be allowed inside the Nyayo National Stadium during the 57th Jamhuri Day celebrations to be led by President Uhuru Kenyatta. This is in line with the strict Covid-19 and Ministry of Health protocols. Photos by Mercy Mumo Only invited guests will be allowed into the venue and no one will gain entry without a mask. Nairobi Regional Commander James Kianda said the ICT ministry will link the rest of Kenya with the event through live television and radio broadcast. Interior PS Karanja Kibicho through a statement to the Regional Commissioners said that the celebrations will only be marked at the Nyayo Stadium in Nairobi, unlike previous celebrations where each county organized the same. Photos by Mercy Mumo